"{\"uid\": \"thesouthafrican.com-lifestyle-celeb-news-local-celebs-mama-joy-chauke-boyfriend-paris-olympics-gayton-mckenzie-latest-news\", \"text\": \"Copyright Blue Sky Publications (Pty) Ltd. All Rights Reserved.  thesouthafrican.com is a division of Blue Sky Publications Ltd. Reproduction without permission prohibited  Home\\u00bbLifestyle\\u00bbCeleb News\\u00bbLocal Celebs\\u00bb'Chest pains!': Mama Joy jets off to the Paris Olympics [photos]  A superfan with a super plan! Mama Joy is bragging about jetting off to the Paris Olympics. But who sponsored her trip?  Mama Joy - real name Joy Chauke - has had the last laugh after posting pictures of her jetting to Paris for the Olympics, which kick off this weekend.  The sports fan - who has been at loggerheads with new Minister of Sport, Arts and Culture Gayton McKenzie after he halted sponsored trips - has been bragging about her trip on her social media accounts.  The Olympicstakes place in Paris from 26 July to 11 August.  On her X account, Mama Joy posted pictures of her posing up a storm at OR Tambo International Airport. The superfan was scheduled to fly out to Paris on Air France on Thursday, 25 July.  Sporting a funky suit and braids in the colours of the South African flag, Chauke posted: \\\"Mama Joy to the Olympics, Paris.\\\"  Addressing her French boyfriend, she added: \\\"Papa Joy, I am coming.\\\"  Chauke tweeted a clip of her bumping into TV sports presenter Carol Tshabalala, who was also en route to the Olympics.  She also retweeted a video of DA leader John Steenhuisen who seemingly approved her plans to attend the sporting tournament.  Mama Joy's \\\"super plan\\\" to get to the Olympics have caught many by surprise, considering her earlier tweets claiming she would be watching the games on her TV set.    Last weekend, Mama Joy bragged about her VIP trip to watch the Springboks play Portugal in Bloemfontein. Chauke revealed that she was staying at a five-star hotel, which had spoiled her with plenty of food and wine.  While Gayton McKenzie has ceased sponsored trips for superfans, many social media users are wondering who paid for Mama Joy to go to the Olympics.  Chest pains \\ud83d\\ude2d  Speaking toeNCAlast week, Chauke claimed that she often footed the bill for her own expenses, which included transport, accommodation, and match tickets.  This time around, tweeps are wondering if the superfan's French lover, whom she met during the Rugby World Cup last year, has anything to do with her trip abroad.  Last week, Mama Joy hinted that theSA sports supporter group, the Braai Army,and travel agent Dan Hooton were responsible for her VIP travel and accommodation to Bloemfontein.  She tweeted: \\\"When I meet \\u2066@BraaiArmy\\u2069 in Paris, I said to myself this is my home. I attended all their events. Today [I] am here at Bon Hotels with them.\\u00a0 Taking care of everything, Dan, Major Danko.\\\"  WIN R2 000: Take The South African's SASSA Survey  The South African is hiring! Freelance writing positions available  Follow The South African on Facebook for the latest local and international news  Follow The South African's WhatsApp channel for the latest sport, lifestyle and local news  Follow The South African on X for the latest, breaking news  A brand new shopping mall is coming to Pretoria East, bringing major retailers and new convenience to the area.  Orlando Pirates are reportedly set to welcome a new staff member in former Stellenbosch FC Head of Recruitment Brendon Fourie.  Masindi Nemtajela was stretched off during Orlando Pirates' 6-0 win over TS Galaxy on Sunday afternoon in Mbombela.  IT support is not just technical, it is personal.  Liema Pantsi's victory was clouded as fans of the 'Big Brother Mzansi' show expressed that Smash Afrika was unprofessional towards her.  A dominant weekend for the SA teams in the URC has made a big impact on the latest log standings as the playoffs edge closer.    TheSouthAfrican.com is all about South Africa and 